HEADWORD: Fermeture
<hw>Fer"me*ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>fermer</ets> to close.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>The mechanism
for closing the breech of a breech-loading firearm, in artillery
consisting principally of the breechblock, obturator, and carrier
ring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

